<p><b>What is ASME B31 3 surge pressure?</b> For example, ASME/ANSI B31. 3 for the chemical and petrochemical plant piping systems specifies a maximum allowable surge pressure of 1.33 times the design pressure of the system. For long distance pipelines, ASME/ANSI B31. 4 specifies 1.1 times the design pressure.</p>
<p><b>What is ASME B31 3 material?</b> ASME B31. 3 specifies the minimum requirements for materials, design, fabrication, testing, and inspection of process piping systems. It covers a wide range of topics, including pipe sizing, pressure design, allowable stresses, corrosion protection, thermal expansion and contraction, and more.</p>
